race.comment: Looks a good race for TSARINE (4) who is fitter for three runs in, placing twice. The latest run narrowly beaten here over 1400m and stretches out to the mile for the first time. Expected to relish the extra ground and should go close. STORM AHEAD (3) has been racing over further and mixing form. Three weeks between runs and back in trip but has early pace and can give a sight. Will run the trip right out. HERE COMES RUBY (5) resumed from a long break with a solid run over 1450m and will appreciate the extra ground. Plenty of upside and drawn for a good run. TIGHT GRIP (7) ran a better race last start, finishing 4 lengths away in seventh over 1600m at Moe. Well placed to turn things around. PIPLUP (9) is fitter for one run back and wasn't far from the winner. Worth including.
